                    <p class="audience">Suggested Audiences: Ages 3-8</p>
                    <p>Simple and bright, <em>The Too Small Elephant</em> empowers young readers to respond to the behavior of others with kindness and understanding. The story of Emmaline, a very small elephant, reveals that sometimes those choosing to hurt others are most in need of our kindness. It takes the brave words of a new friend to inspire Emmaline to face her insecurities. Will her friends forgive her?<br />
